valdiff
Written by Kelly Shaw
4/12/04

Usage:
	perl valdiff.pl --file1=<hist1> --file2=<hist2> [--output=<out>
		--start-index=<num> --end-index=<num> ]

Input:
	--file1, --file2: Files with histograms to compare
	--start-index, --end-index: You can specify which specific part of 
		the histogram you'd like to see where R values go from
		0-255, G from 256-511, etc.

Output:
	stdout: Total error and percent error values
	out: (default is valdiff.output)
             Contains text output of differences

